components.description:
An emoji version of the digit 5, created via a variation selector.

Not given emoji presentation on Apple or Microsoft devices, or on platforms such as Facebook and Twitter / X. Microsoft did previously support this emoji within Windows 8 and Windows 10.

apple_vendor_description: On Apple devices, the '5' keycap emoji presents a crisp, white digit centered within a vibrant blue square, rendered with Apple's signature glossy 3D shading.  The soft, rounded edges of the keycap and the subtle gradient within the blue background give it a polished, tactile feel, evoking the familiar interface of Apple's keyboards.  This emoji is commonly used to represent the number five, numerical lists, or to signify a fifth item or option in digital communication.
